'''''The Toys That Made Us''''' is an American television series created by [[Brian Volk-Weiss]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2017/12/a-toy-story-for-nerds-like-us-netflixs-the-toys-that-made-us-doc-drops-next-week/|title=A toy story for nerds like us—Netflix’s The Toys That Made Us doc drops next week |work=[[Ars Technica]]|accessdate=3 January 2018}}</ref> The first four episodes of the series began streaming on [[Netflix]] on December 22, 2017,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://ew.com/tv/2017/11/20/new-netflix-december-2017/|title=New on Netflix in December: 'The Crown,' 'Fuller House,' and more|work=EW.com|access-date=2017-12-05|language=en}}</ref> and the next four were released in May 25, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2017/12/29/16830220/netflix-the-toys-that-made-us-review-star-wars-barbie-he-man-g-i-joe|title=Netflix's The Toys That Made Us explains how Star Wars changed toys forever|last=Hall|first=Charlie|date=2017-12-29|website=Polygon|access-date=2018-01-02}}</ref> The 8-episode documentary series, as it was originally touted, focuses on the history of important toy lines. The first four episodes focus on the [[Kenner Star Wars action figures|Star Wars]], [[Masters of the Universe|He-Man]], [[Barbie]] and [[G.I. Joe]] toy lines<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/what-to-stream-netflix-amazon-hulu|title=Here’s What’s New to Stream in December on Amazon, Netflix, and Hulu|work=Vogue|access-date=2017-12-05|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.outrightgeekery.com/2017/11/21/toys-made-premiere/|title=Netflix Series THE TOYS THAT MADE US to Premiere on December 22nd - Outright Geekery|date=2017-11-21|work=Outright Geekery|access-date=2017-12-05|language=en-US}}</ref> with subsequent episodes featuring [[Lego|LEGO]], [[Transformers (toy line)|Transformers]], [[Hello Kitty]], and [[Star Trek]],<ref>[https://www.polygon.com/2018/1/10/16875164/the-toys-that-made-us-season-2-release-date-lego-transformers-star-trek-hello-kitty The Toys That Made Us season two will feature Lego, Star Trek and more], Charlie Hall, [[polygon.com]] Posted January 10, 2018, Retrieved February 8, 2018.</ref> which aired on May 25, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://vodzilla.co/blog/coming-soon-to-netflix/whats-coming-soon-to-netflix-uk-in-may-2018/ |title=What's coming soon to Netflix UK in May 2018? |publisher=VOD News |date=April 24, 2018 |accessdate=April 24, 2018}}</ref> On July 19, 2018, it was announced at [[San Diego Comic-Con]] that the show had been picked up for a third season, with episodes featuring [[Power Rangers]], [[Professional wrestling|Wrestling]], [[My Little Pony]], and [[Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bleedingcool.com/2018/07/19/toys-that-made-us-season-3-power-rangers-wrestling-tmnt-my-little-pony/ |title=Toys That Made Us Season 3 Will Feature Power Rangers, Wrestling, TMNT, and My Little Pony |publisher=Bleeding Cool News |date=July 19, 2018 |accessdate=July 19, 2018}}</ref>
